// =============================================================================
// CCGNF — Schema Reference
// =============================================================================
// The six primitives and their metadata. All other constructs in the encoding
// reduce to these primitives. Reference material for the Validator.
//
// --- Primitives
//
// Entity
//   Identified bundle of Characteristics, DerivedCharacteristics, Counters,
//   Tags, a Zone, owner/controller, and Abilities.
//   Kinds: Card, Player, Zone, Phase, Game, Arena, Conduit, Echo, Token,
//          Standard, ContinuousModifier, PlayBinding (ephemeral).
//
// Zone
//   Structured collection of Entities.
//   Parameters:
//     - capacity     : int | unlimited
//     - order        : unordered | LIFO | FIFO | sequential
//     - on_overflow  : reject | EvictLeftmost | EvictOldest
//     - visibility   : public | private_to_owner | face_down
//     - adjacency    : optional relation to other zones
//
// Event
//   Typed record: { type, source, target, payload, phase, timestamp }
//
// Effect
//   Algebraic term over atomic ops and combinators.
//   Atomic ops: DealDamage, Heal, Draw, Mill, MoveTo, PayAether, SetState,
//               ClearState, IncCounter, CreateToken, EmitEvent, NoOp, ...
//   Combinators: Sequence, Choice, ForEach, Target, If, When, Cond,
//                ChooseHighest, ScheduleAt, Replace, Prevent, Repeat, Switch,
//                let..in.
//
// Ability
//   (kind, trigger, guard, cost, effect) tuple attached to an Entity.
//   Kinds: Static, Triggered, OnResolve, Replacement, Activated.
//
// Predicate / Selector
//   Expressions over game state and events. Lambda syntax: `x -> x.cost <= 3`.
//
// --- Characteristic layering
//
// Three layers, applied in order:
//   1. Base / Copy       — initial characteristic values; Copy(other) effects.
//   2. Stat modifiers    — +N/+N, Fortify, ongoing +Force, Ramparts reductions.
//   3. Ability grants    — "gains Sentinel", "loses all abilities".
//
// Queries against a characteristic run through all three layers before
// returning a value. Static abilities can sit at any layer; Triggered and
// OnResolve abilities produce concrete one-shot modifiers at layer 2.
